===Etymology 1===
{{inh+|ro|la|sīc||thus, so, like, in this way}}. Compare {{cog|rup|shi}}, {{cog|ruq|și}}.
Possibly related to {{cog|it|sia|pos=originally a subjunctive form of {{m|it|essere}} “to be”}} as in the construction {{m|it||sia … sia …|both … and …}}, which is equivalent to Romanian {{m|ro||și … și …}}. {{rfv-etym|ro}}

====Conjunction====
{{ro-conjunction}}

# {{lb|ro|connecting words or sentences}} [[and]]
#: {{syn|ro|iar<q:only connecting sentences>|i<q:obsolete>}}
#: {{ux|ro|În sertar sunt hârtii '''și''' câteva pixuri '''și''' creioane.|In the drawer there are papers '''and''' a few pens '''and''' pencils.}}
## {{ng|Connects the nonzero digit in the ones place to the rest of a number greater than 20, the way a hyphen does in English writing, or a fraction to the whole.}}
##: {{ux|ro|Am în cont douăzeci '''și''' trei de mii șase sute patruzeci '''și''' unu de lei.|I have twenty'''-'''three thousand six hundred forty'''-'''one lei in my account.}}
##: {{ux|ro|― Câte ture ai alergat? ― Două '''și''' jumătate.|“How many laps did you run?” “Two '''and''' a half.”}}
## {{ng|Used as a question by itself in dialogue to mean “and what?”.}}
## {{lb|ro|informal}} {{ng|Connects two items in close causal connection and a one-to-one proportion, typically in elliptical sentences.}}
##: {{ux|ro|În Japonia, procesul '''și''' condamnarea.|In Japan, '''for every''' trial a conviction.}}
##: {{ux|ro|Nu este realist în marketingul telefonic apelul '''și''' vânzarea.|A sale '''for every''' call is unrealistic in telephone marketing.}}
##: {{ux|ro|În toamna lui 1940, în Londra era ziua '''și''' bombardamentul.|In the autumn of 1940, in London there would be an air raid '''every''' day.}}
## {{lb|ro|informal}} {{ng|Ironically, within an exclamation, connects a topic of discussion with a trait or association deemed incompatible.}}
##: {{ux|ro|„Republica Democrată Germană”? Ei '''și''' democrația!|“German Democratic Republic”? They '''and''' democracy—what a joke!}}
## {{ng|Placed between two repetitions of a noun to remark on the diversity in the ranks of said noun.}}
##: {{ux|ro|Orice profesor știe că există copii '''și''' copii.|Any teacher knows there are all sorts of children.|lit=children '''and''' children}}
## {{ng|Placed between two repetitions of a word to signify incessantness.}}
##: {{ux|ro|Temperatura urcă '''și''' urcă.|The temperature rises '''and''' rises.}}
# {{lb|ro|Northwestern|_|Transylvania}} {{syn of|ro|să}}: [[to]], [[in order to]]

